segment.source: After you sequence an application but before you save it, you can use the following procedure to manually modify the sequenced application package.
segment.target: After you sequence an application but before you save it, you can use the following procedure to manually modify the sequenced application package.

segment.source: To remove an embedded service
segment.target: To remove an embedded service

segment.source: Click the Virtual Services tab.
segment.target: Click the Virtual Services tab.

segment.source: Right-click the service you want to remove, and select Remove.
segment.target: Right-click the service you want to remove, and select Remove.

segment.source: In the Sequencer dialog box, click Yes.
segment.target: In the Sequencer dialog box, click Yes.

segment.source: To modify the properties of an embedded service
segment.target: To modify the properties of an embedded service

segment.source: Click the Virtual Services tab.
segment.target: Click the Virtual Services tab.

segment.source: Right-click the service whose properties you want to modify, and select Properties.
segment.target: Right-click the service whose properties you want to modify, and select Properties.

segment.source: In the Office Source Engine Properties dialog box, complete the following tasks:
segment.target: In the Office Source Engine Properties dialog box, complete the following tasks:

segment.source: In the Display Name text box, type the name of the service.
segment.target: In the Display Name text box, type the name of the service.

segment.source: In the Description text box, type a description of the service.
segment.target: In the Description text box, type a description of the service.

segment.source: In the Path to Executable text box, enter the path to the executable file.
segment.target: In the Path to Executable text box, enter the path to the executable file.

segment.source: From the Startup Type drop down list, select how the service is to start up—manually, automatically, or not.
segment.target: From the Startup Type drop down list, select how the service is to start up—manually, automatically, or not.

segment.source: Click OK.
segment.target: Click OK.
